Privacy Policy - Worktree
Effective Date: June 18, 2025
Last Updated: June 18, 2025

At Worktree, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our platform.

1. Information We Collect
Information You Provide Directly
Account Information: Name, email address, password, profile picture
Profile Information: University, major, graduation year, GPA, coursework, academic honors
Career Information: Work experience, internships, certifications, career goals, job preferences
Learning Preferences: Skills interests, learning style, project preferences, time commitment
Professional Details: Work authorization status, security clearance, languages spoken
Information from Third-Party Services
LinkedIn Integration: When you connect your LinkedIn account, we may access:
Basic profile information (name, headline, profile picture)
Work experience and employment history
Education details
Skills and endorsements
Professional certifications
Industry and location information
Automatically Collected Information
Usage Data: How you interact with our platform, pages visited, features used
Device Information: Browser type, operating system, IP address
Cookies and Tracking: Session data, preferences, analytics information
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:

Core Services
Create and manage your account
Provide personalized career guidance through our AI assistant "Sprig"
Match you with relevant projects and opportunities
Track your skill development and progress
Generate your dynamic skill tree visualization
Platform Improvement
Analyze usage patterns to improve our services
Develop new features and functionality
Conduct research and analytics
Ensure platform security and prevent fraud
Communication
Send important account notifications
Provide customer support
Share relevant opportunities and updates
Respond to your inquiries
3. Information Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information in limited circumstances:

With Your Consent
When you explicitly authorize sharing with specific partners or employers
When you choose to make profile information public
Service Providers
Third-party services that help us operate our platform (hosting, analytics, email)
These providers are bound by confidentiality agreements
Legal Requirements
When required by law, regulation, or legal process
To protect the rights, property, or safety of Worktree, our users, or others
In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets
4. LinkedIn Integration
Data Access
When you connect your LinkedIn account:

We only access data necessary for profile auto-fill functionality
You can review and edit all imported information before saving
Connection is optional and can be revoked at any time
Data Usage
LinkedIn data is used to:

Pre-populate your Worktree profile fields
Suggest relevant career paths and opportunities
Enhance AI-powered recommendations
Third-Party Terms
Your use of LinkedIn integration is also governed by LinkedIn's Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.

5. Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures:

Encryption: Data is encrypted in transit and at rest
Access Controls: Limited access to personal information on a need-to-know basis
Regular Audits: Security practices are regularly reviewed and updated
Secure Infrastructure: Platform hosted on secure, monitored servers
6. Data Retention
Account Information: Retained while your account is active
Profile Data: Stored until you delete your account or request removal
Usage Analytics: Aggregated data may be retained for analytical purposes
Legal Compliance: Some data may be retained longer to meet legal obligations
7. Your Rights and Choices
Account Management
Access: View and download your personal information
Update: Modify your profile and preferences at any time
Delete: Request account deletion and data removal
Privacy Controls
LinkedIn Disconnect: Revoke LinkedIn integration at any time
Data Portability: Export your data in a machine-readable format
Communication Preferences: Opt out of non-essential communications
Exercising Your Rights
Contact us at privacy@worktree.com to exercise any of these rights.

8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar technologies for:

Essential Functions: Authentication, security, basic functionality
Analytics: Understanding platform usage and performance
Preferences: Remembering your settings and preferences
You can control cookies through your browser settings, though some features may not work properly if disabled.

9. International Data Transfers
If you access Worktree from outside the United States, your information may be transferred to and processed in the United States. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place for such transfers.

10. Children's Privacy
Worktree is designed for college students and is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will:

Post the updated policy on this page
Update the "Last Updated" date
Notify you of significant changes via email or platform notification
Maintain previous versions for your reference
12. Contact Information
Data Protection Officer
For privacy-related questions or concerns:

Email: privacy@worktree.com
Address: [Your Address - Update when available]
General Support
For platform support and general inquiries:

Email: support@worktree.com
Platform: Through the Worktree contact form
13. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)
For users in the European Economic Area, we process your personal information based on:

Consent: When you explicitly consent to specific processing activities
Contract Performance: To provide our services as outlined in our Terms of Service
Legitimate Interests: To improve our platform and provide personalized experiences
Legal Compliance: To meet our legal obligations
14. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)
California residents have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act:

Right to know what personal information is collected
Right to delete personal information
Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information
Right to non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights
We do not sell personal information as defined by CCPA.

Development Notice
This privacy policy is designed for the Worktree platform currently in development. Some features and data practices described may not yet be fully implemented. This policy will be updated as the platform evolves.

For questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at the information provided above.
